SubmitterDescription.SubmitterName: International Standards For Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium (ISCA)

SampleDescription.Description: Metaphase FISH studies using a probe within the duplicated interval (CTD-2117A4) demonstrated that the duplicated material is present on a supernumerary marker or small ring chromosome. This supernumerary marker chromosome was observed in 3 of 30 metaphases (10.0%) and 22.0% of interphase nuclei from a PHA-stimulated culture as well as 28.0% of interphase nuclei from a direct preparation.

ClinicalAssertion.StudyDescription: Copy number variation identified through the course of routine clinical cytogenomic testing in postnatal populations, with clinical assertions as classified by the original submitter.
